      <gmd:abstract><gco:CharacterString>The NOAA MDBC Mapping, Groundtruthing and Modeling team conducted an Uncrewed Underwater Vehicle (UUV) survey aboard NOAA Ship Point Sur during Leg 18 (PS2418L0) on 5 May 2024. The Eagle Ray UUV equipped with a Norbit iWBMS Wide-Band Multibeam Sonar (MBES) collected high-resolution bathymetric data along pre-planned dive tracks in the Gulf of Mexico. Survey objectives included seafloor characterization and habitat mapping in support of MDBC restoration assessment. Data were acquired in WGS84/EPSG:4326, processed to NetCDF, and archived at NCEI under accession 0289741.</gco:CharacterString></gmd:abstract>
      <gmd:purpose><gco:CharacterString>Seafloor mapping and habitat characterization in support of NOAA MDBC Mesophotic and Deep Benthic Communities restoration assessment program.</gco:CharacterString></gmd:purpose>
